ActionIconButton.tsx — A small rounded action button used in the tab strip: takes an optional icon node and/or a tiny mono text label, an aria/title label, and renders in one of three tones — primary (indigo border and wash), danger (red text with a red hover wash), or the default muted gray — respecting a disabled state.

CodeEditor.tsx — Wrapper around codemirror 6 that mounts an EditorView into a div and keeps it in sync with react props.
Configures basicSetup, a dark editor theme (13px mono, #101317 background, indigo cursor and selection), a bright custom highlight style over lezer tags, optional python language support when mode is "python", line wrapping, a dimmed read-only variant, and optional autofocus.
Acts as a controlled component: external value changes are dispatched into the document with a suppress flag so they do not echo back through onChange, and cursor/selection changes are reported out while an external selection prop is clamped, applied only when the view is unfocused, and scrolled into view.
Highlights two things through reconfigurable compartments: highlightedLines get a translucent yellow full-line decoration and the first one scrolls to center, while highlightedRanges get indigo origin-range marks with a stronger underlined hover style tracking the narrowest range under the pointer whenever ctrl/meta is held, updated on mousemove/mouseleave and recomputed when the ranges change.
Ctrl/meta-click and ctrl/meta-right-click resolve the document position under the pointer and invoke onModClick / onModContextMenu callbacks with the position, line number, and line text, preventing the default behavior.

ConfirmDeleteModal.tsx — A fixed full-screen overlay with a centered card asking "Delete {title}?", showing a description paragraph and a mono detail line, with cancel and red delete buttons that both respect a disabled flag.

DiffPreview.tsx — Renders a unified diff between a saved "before" text and a draft "after" text using MultiFileDiff from @pierre/diffs, memoizing both sides as FileContents with cache keys derived from a small djb2-style hash, an optional language, pierre dark/light themes, bar indicators, word-level line diffing, and scroll overflow.

ExplorerSidebar.tsx — The sticky 260px sidebar shell, wrapped in Suspense because it reads an optional ?path= search param that overrides the workspace root.
Its header links back to the project list showing the active project name, with a collapse-all control that resets expansion; an EXPLORER strip offers new-item creation controls whose inline submission calls the fs create endpoint, refreshes, and opens the made entry (or expands the made directory).
Fetches the top level of the workspace via the fs listing endpoint on mount and whenever the refresh keys change, tracks expanded/selected state, forwards opens and right-click positions upward with its workspace root path attached to every open, created-file, and delete request, shows a floating menu with a single Delete entry, lets the Delete key request removal of the current selection outside inputs, and renders extra children below (the history panel slot).

FileTree.tsx — The recursive tree rows for the sidebar: a name.human entry with a sibling name.context collapses into a pair row that hides the standalone context and nests it beneath a chevron, generated .context/.py entries carry an eye badge and dimmed coloring while .human names render bright, directories lazy-load their children one level at a time on expand and remember open state, an inline create row commits on enter and cancels on escape or blur showing any server error, and every row supports click-to-select-and-open, hover/selection backgrounds, indentation by depth, and right-click reporting for the floating menu.
Every open reports whether the clicked file is paired with a .human sibling — true for a .human itself, for the clickable nested context row of a pair, and for a .context or .py file whose same-base .human sits in the same folder — and the active-row highlight matches the active file by full path or trailing path suffix rather than by bare filename.

icons.tsx — The hand-drawn 16px stroke svg set: document glyphs for human text, python (filled bar), json-like braces, and markdown, folder and open-folder shapes, left/right/down chevrons, an eye, new-file and new-folder glyphs, a collapse-all glyph, and sparkles, all typed over SVGProps; also exports ICON_BY_EXTENSION mapping .human, .context, .py, and .md to their glyphs.
